An activist on Monday was beaten and thrown into Lake Victoria after he was accused of conning Kisumu residents.Bernard Odinga (pictured) of Agulu Environment Network was accused of conning 560 residents out of Sh500 each in 2013. The residents paid the money as fee to be hired for a project to manually remove the water hyacinth in Lake Victoria. He was accosted as he launched the same project with another group at the same place he had acquired money from the 560.